    <enumeration name="SymmetryOffset"
                 glib:type-name="IpuzSymmetryOffset"
                 glib:get-type="ipuz_symmetry_offset_get_type"
                 c:type="IpuzSymmetryOffset">
      <doc xml:space="preserve"
           filename="libipuz/ipuz-symmetry.h"
           line="55">Offset off the mode of symmetry.

Some symmetries have four points of symmetry, others two. When
trying to calculate the symmetry, this detail can be used to
indicate which one is being requested.

The following types can have four points of symmetry:
[enum@Ipuz.Symmetry.ROTATIONAL_QUARTER] and
[enum@Ipuz.Symmetry.MIRRORED].</doc>
      <member name="opposite"
              value="0"
              c:identifier="IPUZ_SYMMETRY_OFFSET_OPPOSITE"
              glib:nick="opposite"
              glib:name="IPUZ_SYMMETRY_OFFSET_OPPOSITE">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libipuz/ipuz-symmetry.h"
             line="57">Opposite cell across the mode of symmetry</doc>
      </member>
      <member name="cw_adjacent"
              value="1"
              c:identifier="IPUZ_SYMMETRY_OFFSET_CW_ADJACENT"
              glib:nick="cw-adjacent"
              glib:name="IPUZ_SYMMETRY_OFFSET_CW_ADJACENT">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libipuz/ipuz-symmetry.h"
             line="58">Clockwise adjacent point</doc>
      </member>
